{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}So when David rose up in the morning, then the word of Jehovah came to the prophet Gad, David\uc1\u8217*s seer, saying,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8220*Go and speak to David, \uc1\u8216*Thus saith Jehovah, \uc1\u8220*Three things I offer thee; choose one of them, that I may do it to thee.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Gad came to David and told him, and said to him, \uc1\u8220*Shall  years of famine come over your land? Or will you flee three months before your foes, while they pursue you? Or shall there be three days\uc1\u8217* pestilence in your land? Now take counsel and consider what answer I shall return to him who sent me.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And David said to Gad, \uc1\u8220*I am in a great strait. We would rather fall into the hand of Jehovah, for his mercy is great, but let me not fall into the hand of man.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}So  of the people from Dan to Beersheba seventy thousand men.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}And when the Messenger stretched out his hand toward Jerusalem to destroy it, Jehovah repented of the evil, and said to the Messenger who was destroying the people, \uc1\u8220*Enough, now stay thy hand!\uc1\u8221* and the Messenger of Jehovah was by the threshing-floor of Araunah the Jebusite.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And David spoke to Jehovah when he saw the Messenger who smote the people, and said, \uc1\u8220*See I have sinned and have acted wickedly; but these sheep, what have they done? Let thy hand, I pray, be against me, and my father\uc1\u8217*s house.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And Gad came that day to David, and said to him, \uc1\u8220*Go up, rear an altar to Jehovah on the threshing-floor of Araunah the Jebusite.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}So David went up at the command of Gad, as Jehovah commanded.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And when Araunah looked down and saw the king and his servants crossing over to him, Araunah went out and bowed before the king with his face to the ground.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}And Araunah said, \uc1\u8220*Why has my lord the king come to his servant?\uc1\u8221* And David said, \uc1\u8220*To buy the threshing-floor of you, to build an altar to Jehovah, that the plague may be averted from the people.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And Araunah said to David, \uc1\u8220*Let my lord the king take and offer what he pleases, the oxen for the burnt-offering, and the threshing-sledges and the implements of the oxen for the wood.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}All this has y king, given to the king.\uc1\u8221* And Araunah said to the king, \uc1\u8220*Jehovah your God accept you!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And the king answered Araunah, \uc1\u8220*No, but I will surely buy it of you at a price. I must not offer burnt-offerings to Jehovah my God which cost me nothing.\uc1\u8221* So David bought the threshing-floor and the oxen for fifty shekels of silver.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Then David built there an altar to Jehovah, and offered burnt-offerings. So Jehovah was entreated for the land and the plague was averted from Israel.
